variables.value: It should be somewhere here in the Football Gardens.\nIt's probably a bit beat-up by now.
You'll find 'em near the lodging area.\nThey're called Saltherb, Emberroot, and Molasmoss.
I'm sure others have seen it too.\nGather their stories and uncover the truth!
The other night, I saw a mysterious floating shape by the beach.\nMust be the restless spirit of a losing player.
Y-You think I'm scared?! Ridiculous! I'm not scared one bit!
So what if I saw a talking soul at night?!\nThat's not enough to faze me!
Thanks! I'll get this in him right away.
We keep our drinks perpetually frosty and crisp,\nso staff and players alike can feel refreshed at any time!
Heh! Snuck in again! So many stars here,\nI don't know who to ask first!
Ah! You're from <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>...\nuh... I know you!
I'll handle the report\nfor the teacher.
I could go for\na bagel sandwich.
Our captain's wandered off again.\nHappens all the time. She'll be back before practice, I bet.
I still can't get used to these huge malls...\nnothing like this back home.
That limited-edition burger's callin' my name,\nbut the strawberry parfait's just as tempting... I'm totally torn!
There's a quiet charm to reading as people pass by.\nWhen I'm really into a story, it soothes and centers me.
When kindred rivals clash, they're often more evenly matched than expected.\nI look forward to seeing where the differences are.
In the semifinals, it felt as if you were weaving a living tale.\nI can't wait to see how it ends... My heart stirs with excitement.
We've already predicted\nthe questions using AI.
We're ready for anything\nthey throw at us.
Was this all\npart of the plan?
Looks like we're in\nfor a good match.
We're guiding folks from the station to the Gardens!\nIt's not just players. There are media and staff too!
If you need help\nfinding your way...
The people in blue are tournament volunteers!\nWe've come from all over to help out!
The Football Gardens are seriously huge!\nEven new staff get lost at first!
Let me know\nif you need anything!
The Royal Academy team showed up in an armored vehicle!\nI only caught a glimpse, but it looked intense!
It's nerve-wracking with reporters coming from overseas.\nFootball Frontier really is a global phenomena!
This place is packed today! Have you spoken with any of them?\nI heard even folks from sports brands are here too!
The building with the Ferris wheel in the back? That's the mall.\nIf your feet are tired, a sweet treat's a great pick-me-up!
I was wandering around and suddenly realized I was alone...\nWe were supposed to share that strawberry yogurt parfait!
Do you know where\nI can find Magic Moves?
Magic Moves is in the basement, and Kool Kit's on the second floor.\nMight be fun to check them out before your match!
I was running an errand for a friend, but this place is huge.\nI totally got lost. I asked a staff member though,\nso I should be good now!
I recommend the Inazuma National Juice. It's a Gardens favorite!\nBlue soda with white ice cream, just like the team colors.
I asked for directions and got a bonus tip too!\nThat Inazuma National Juice sounds like it could power me up.\nMaybe I'll give it a try.
Just hearing "Grand Finals" makes my heart race.\nFamily members can enter the Gardens, right?\nMaybe I'll ask mine to come...
There are so many TV crews here at the Football Gardens...\nJust knowing we're in the spotlight makes me even more nervous.
My AI-made Gardens route got deleted...\nGuess I'll just start at the donut shop and wing it from there.
You can find just\nabout anything here...
I'm still kinda down about losing to Royal Academy,\nbut visiting one of the AI-recommended shops helped take my mind off it.
I followed the AI gourmet plan, and now I can't move...\nThe burger and parfait were amazing, though!
I used AI to pick a souvenir ahead of time,\nbut now that I'm seeing everything in person, I can't choose...\nIt's all so good!
This place will look\ngreat on camera.
Might snag some\ninterviews in the plaza!
We could use\nthis for a segment.
If it topples, it's\na broadcast disaster?!
If that happens,\nI'll cover for you!
Let's try to get\na memorable quote!
I'd love to feature\nit in a segment!
I want to highlight the\ncheering section too.
I'd love to show off\nthe fan merch.
You can really see\nthe staff's hard work.
I'm sure the players\ncan relax a little too.
The staff seem to be\nenjoying themselves too.
Everything looks so good. I can't decide!\nMaybe I'll go with the Dream Tower. Seven flavors in one!
The limited-edition flavor is shaped like a football!\nIt's got berries too, and looks absolutely yummy.\nI think I'll order it!
One of the big players from <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> was tackling the Dream Tower!\nWatching him enjoy it made me want one too!
Feeling peckish? Come check out G-Mart's selection!\nWe've got hot, freshly fried snacks!
Tried the football-shaped burger yet? Thick, juicy,\nand a total showstopper. Only at the Gardens!
Our new ice cream crepe is chilled and chewy!\nSweet-tart strawberry, and creamy-rich chocolate. It's got it all!
Thirsty? Our super-fizzy soda is just the thing!\nRefreshing enough to boost your mood too!
The combo meals\nare a great deal!
Add a side to your burger! It's a way better deal as a set!
There are open seats\nin the back!
Feel free to sit\nwherever you like!
We've got hot snacks, red bean buns, cream puffs, even rice balls!\nSweet or savory. You've got options!
Let us know\nif you need help!
The players seem\nto like it too.
Our product showed up\nin one of their posts.
I'm a little worn out\nfrom walking...
Hey! You're one of the <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> players, right?\nThey love CHAMP-ON in Nagasaki!
I'm a big fan,\nbut those new limited-edition boots are really hard to find.
Whoa, no way. Is that the latest limited pair?!\nThey look even cooler in person!!
Thanks for showing me.\nI'm gonna work hard and snag a pair for myself too!
I should've just given her\na phone...
Where could she have gone? She did say she wanted to see the pond...
Huh? My mom's looking for me?\nThanks for letting me know. I'll head back right away!
